The paper deals with lower bounds for dynamic data structure problems, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The problems considered in the paper are related to text indexing (cs.DM), graph algorithms (cs.CG), and distance oracles (cs.DL), which are all sub-fields of algorithms and data structures. The paper also uses reductions from the 3SUM problem, which is a well-known problem in computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
